default1.2 The AAA remains opposed to academy conversions. We are not opposed to schools – once they have become aca
defaultdemies. We want every school to flourish. Howeve
defaultr 
defaultwe continue to reject the political ideology that lies behind academy conversion – voluntary or forced. In essence academy conversion is about a ‘supply-side revolution’
default (a
defaults the 2009 Tory party manifesto 
defaultnoted). It seeks to open up the public sector to private interests. Yet there remains no credible evidence that this leads to sustained improvement in schools. Th
defaultus th
defaulte Secretary of State’s political ideology is trumping evidence based policy. It is aliena
defaultting parents and staff, but worse still it threatens 
defaultthe best interest of this and future 
defaultgeneration
defaults of children
default.
default The sobering experience of two decades of market driven reforms in Sweden should be 
defaultenough to
default persuade the government to halt these reforms. 
defaultRegrettably, the Coalition is unwilling to listen at the moment. We hope the Select Committee can help make them take note.
